sentences: Creep (stylized as CREÆŽP) is a Brooklyn based electronic music duo formed in 2009.
In 2009, Lauren Flax and Lauren Dillard formed CREEP after having been in projects together before.
In January 2011, their second single "You", featuring Nina Sky, was released.
On January 26, 2011, the music video for the song "Days" was released on Young Turks' official YouTube account.
On May 15, 2011, the music video for "You" was released on the duo's official website.
In December 2011, "Animals" was released along with its music video.
It was released as an official single on January 17, 2012.

In 2013, they released three singles from their debut album: "Call Her" (featuring Tricky and Alejandra De La Deheza of School of Seven Bells, "Vertigo" (featuring Lou Rhodes of Lamb) and "Dim the Lights" (featuring Sia).
All singles were released from album Echoes"Days" (released on December 19, 2010) (Creep featuring Romy Madley Croft) (Young Turks)

CREEP are best known for their singles "Days" (featuring Romy Madley Croft of the XX)  and "You," in collaboration with popular American duo Nina Sky on their debut album Echoes.
Before the release of "Days" (featuring Romy XX), they started their own label, 'CREEP INTL.'.
On January 26, 2011, the music video for the song "Days" was released on Young Turks' official YouTube account.
Late in the year, Flax revealed she was openly lesbian and CREEP continued with recording of their first album.
2012-present:
The album, Echoes was initially announced for an August 2013 release.
It was eventually released worldwide on November 12.
